text: The 2026 Victorian state election will probably be held on 28 November 2026 to elect the 61st Parliament of Victoria, including all 88 seats in the Legislative Assembly and all 40 seats in the Legislative Council. It will be conducted by the Victorian Electoral Commission. The incumbent Labor government, led by Premier Daniel Andrews, will try and win a fourth consecutive term in government, opposed by the Liberal/National Coalition, led by John Pesutto. ==Notes== ==References== Category:Elections in Victoria Category:2026 elections Category:Future elections Category:2020s in Australia
title: 2026 Victorian state election
